message.content:
A 'Lonicera tatarica' is a deciduous shrub from the honeysuckle family.
It can grow up to 4 meters tall and 3 meters wide.
The leaves are opposite, elliptical, and about 3-8 cm long.
Its flowers bloom in late spring to early summer and are pink to red in color.
The fruit is a small red berry.
It is commonly used as an ornamental plant in gardens and parks.
It can also be found in natural habitats such as slopes and riverbanks.
